Explanation:

The problem requires finding the minimum number of steps to remove all palindromic subsequences from the given string. We can solve this by iterating through the string and removing the last character each time until the string becomes empty. The time complexity is O(n), where n is the length of the string, as we iterate through the string once. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space to store the length of the string and the steps variable. There are no energy implications as the solution only involves CPU operations.

